families%2C%20including%20lowering%20childcare%20costs%2C%20student%20loan%20forgiveness%2C%20and%20tax%20credits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20has%20rallied%20behind%20Walz's%20background%20growing%20up%20in%20rural%20Nebraska%2C%20serving%20in%20the%20military%2C%20and%20working%20as%20a%20high%20school%20teacher%20and%20coach.%20According%20to%20his%202023%20tax%20returns%2C%20Walz%20and%20his%20wife%20had%20a%20total%20income%20of%20about%20%24299%2C000%2C%20relatively%20modest%20for%20a%20politician%20with%20a%20national%20profile.%20Walz's%20comparably%20low%20net%20wealth%20has%20drawn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftim-walz-net-worth-164e5da6%3Fmod%3Dwknd_pos1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epraise%20and%20criticism%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVance%2C%20a%20Marine%20veteran%2C%20wrote%20the%20memoir%20%26quot%3BHillbilly%20Elegy%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20documents%20going%20up%20in%20Ohio%20and%20Kentucky%20in%20a%20family%20struggling%20to%20put%20food%20on%20the%20table.%20Vance%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20venture%20capitalist%2C%20recently%20criticized%20Harris%20for%20wearing%20expensive%20jewelry.%20Vance%2C%20backed%20by%20Silicon%20Valley%20billionaires%20such%20as%20Peter%20Thiel%2C%20and%20his%20wife%20listed%20between%20%244.4%20million%20to%20%2411.5%20million%20in%20assets%20in%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F08%2F09%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fwalz-vance-money.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20just%20one%20problem%3A%20The%20middle%20class%20they're%20trying%20to%20cater%20to%20doesn't%20really%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20many%20Americans%20earn%20somewhere%20in%20the%20middle%20band%20of%20incomes.%20But%20as%20much%20as%20the%20middle%20class%20is%20discussed%2C%20there%20isn't%20any%20official%20or%20well-defined%20economic%20idea%20of%20what%20being%20middle%20class%20means.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClass%20is%20a%20very%20strange%20concept%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeffrey%20Wenger%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20the%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20a%20very%20class-conscious%20people%20in%20general%2C%20so%20we%20have%20very%20loose%20conceptions%20of%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20a%20class%20and%20the%20kinds%20of%20consumption%20behaviors%2C%20attitudes%2C%20and%20all%20of%20the%20other%20things%20that%20come%20along%20with%20notions%20of%20class.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20not%20having%20well-defined%20boundaries%2C%20Americans%20historically%20like%20to%20identify%20themselves%20as%20being%20in%20the%20middle%20class.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F645281%2Fsteady-americans-identify-middle-class.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20that%20in%202024%2C%20only%202%25%20of%20Americans%20consider%20themselves%20upper%20class%2C%20while%20only%2012%25%20think%20they're%20lower%20class.%20Meanwhile%2C%2054%25%20say%20they're%20upper-middle%20or%20middle%20class%2C%20while%2031%25%20identify%20as%20working%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20can%20likely%20be%20chalked%20up%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20the%20neutrality%20and%20connotation%20of%20the%20label%20%E2%80%94%20middle-class%20evokes%20a%20hard%20worker%2C%20but%20not%20one%20who%20has%20fallen%20into%20poverty%20or%20earns%20exorbitant%20amounts%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F0xglF%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22What%20social%20class%20Americans%20identify%20with%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22437%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20poor%2C%20they%20aspire%20to%20be%20middle%20class%20because%20that's%20the%20norm%2C%20and%20for%20the%20wealthy%2C%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20the%20robber%20barons%20and%20the%20targets%20of%20'tax%20the%20rich%2C'%26quot%3B%20Wenger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245217a7f-a248-4aaf-bcf9-5f5f9e9855a9%5C%22%3EWho%20is%20middle%20class%20in%20America%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20simplest%20way%20to%20measure%20the%20middle%20class%20is%20to%20take%20the%20middle%2050%25%20of%20the%20national%20income%20distribution.%20The%20problem%20with%20this%2C%20Wenger%20said%2C%20is%20that%20you%20can't%20determine%20if%20the%20middle%20class%20is%20shrinking%20or%20growing%2C%20as%20it%20will%20always%20be%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPew%20Research%20Center%20defines%20middle-income%20earners%20as%20Americans%20making%20between%20two-thirds%20to%20double%20the%20median%20income%20for%20their%20family%20size%3B%20that%20group%20has%20been%20shrinking%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-it-takes-to-be-middle-class-middle-income-wealth-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20more%20Americans%20rising%20into%20the%20upper%20class%20by%20that%20definition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPew%20found%20that%20the%20share%20of%20middle-class%20Americans%20fell%20from%2061%25%20in%201971%20to%2051%25%20in%202023.%20In%202023%2C%2019%25%20of%20Americans%20are%20upper-income%2C%20while%2030%25%20are%20lower-income.%20But%20despite%20more%20formerly%20middle%20class%20Americans%20being%20better%20off%20today%2C%20many%20wouldn't%20identify%20as%20upper%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20talk%20to%20all%20the%20people%20who%20earn%20two%20times%20the%20median%20income%2C%20which%20is%20about%20%24150%2C000%20today%20in%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20most%20would%20not%20say%20that%20they're%20wealthy%20or%20upper%20class%2C%26quot%3B%20Wenger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F0Dm80%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Upper%20and%20lower%20boundaries%20for%20being%20middle-class%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22347%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20partially%20because%20this%20measurement%20depends%20on%20what%20your%20income%20can%20buy%2C%20Wenger%20added.%20A%20family%20making%20%2475%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20Kansas%20will%20be%20more%20comfortable%20financially%20than%20an%20identical%20family%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20Plus%2C%20homeownership%2C%20insurance%2C%20and%20access%20to%20education%20have%20all%20gotten%20more%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20those%20who%20might%20qualify%20as%20middle%20class%20on%20income%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20three%20big%20things%20that%20help%20stabilize%20middle-class%20families%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20consumption%20have%20all%20gotten%20a%20lot%20more%20expensive%20relative%20to%20median%20incomes%2C%26quot%3B%20Wenger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20better%20define%20the%20middle%20class%20based%20on%20the%20lifestyle%20it%20can%20afford%2C%20Wenger%20and%20his%20colleagues%20developed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs11205-022-02977-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumption-based%20measure%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20found%20that%20just%2055%25%20of%20people%20considered%20middle-class%20based%20on%20income%20are%20also%20middle-class%20according%20to%20their%20consumption%20measurement.%20The%20model%20analyzes%20the%20percentage%20of%20after-tax%20household%20income%20that%20goes%20toward%20necessity%20spending%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bfood%2C%20housing%2C%20healthcare%2C%20education%2C%20childcare%2C%20transportation%2C%20personal%20care%2C%20and%20apparel.%26quot%3B%20Middle-class%20households%20spend%2040%25%20to%2090%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20necessities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20measure%20of%20the%20middle%20class%20is%20more%20qualitative%2C%20pegged%20to%20their%20role%20in%20society%20or%20their%20economic%20aspirations.%20Some%20consider%20themselves%20middle-class%20if%20they%20own%20a%20modest%20home%2C%20have%20enough%20to%20care%20for%20their%20children%2C%20or%20take%20vacations%20every%20now%20and%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20consider%20themselves%20middle-class%20if%20they%20work%20in%20middle-skilled%20jobs%2C%20often%20characterized%20by%20clerical%20tasks.%20They%20could%20be%20members%20of%20what%20researchers%20Barbara%20and%20John%20Ehrenreich%20termed%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flibrary.brown.edu%2Fpdfs%2F1125403552886481.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessional-managerial%20class%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3A%20Knowledge%20workers%20on%20salary%20who%20spend%20their%20days%20producing%20mental%20work%20in%20places%20like%20universities%20or%20digital%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20distinct%20from%20working-class%2C%20blue-collar%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20yet%2C%20as%20Ehrenreich%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dissentmagazine.org%2Fonline_articles%2Fon-the-origins-of-the-professional-managerial-class-an-interview-with-barbara-ehrenreich%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20fate%20that%20befell%20the%20blue-collar%20workers%20who%20had%20jobs%20shipped%20away%20and%20union%20benefits%20dissipate%20has%20now%20inflicted%20the%20professional%20class.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20turntables%20are%20tilting%20back%20toward%20America's%20blue-collar%20workers%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-collar-job-demand-growth-white-collar-layoffs-ai-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emight%20have%20more%20of%20a%20claim%20to%20the%20middle-class%20moniker%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20they%20have%20in%20the%20past%20five%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cad91829-6bdd-4255-978b-aab6bb5c8f1a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20middle-class%20Americans%20are%20struggling%20to%20get%20by%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20federal%20government's%20take%20on%20who%20should%20be%20eligible%20for%20different%20forms%20of%20social%20assistance%20belies%20a%20misunderstanding%20of%20what%20salary%20makes%20Americans%20economically%20comfortable.%20Fewer%20Americans%20live%20in%20the%20official%20definition%20of%20poverty%2C%20but%20more%20are%20increasingly%20joining%20the%20ranks%20of%20ALICE%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20they're%20asset-limited%2C%20income-constrained%2C%20but%20employed.%20Those%20are%20Americans%20who%20make%20too%20much%20money%20to%20qualify%20for%20social%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20and%20might%20even%20fall%20within%20the%20income%20constraints%20of%20middle-income%20%E2%80%94%20but%20still%20aren't%20getting%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20many%20older%20Americans%20don't%20have%20stable%20income%20aside%20from%20Social%20Security%20or%20pensions%2C%20they%20may%20be%20considered%20lower-class%20based%20on%20strict%20income-based%20measurements.%20However%2C%20their%20consumption%20habits%20may%20suggest%20that%20they%20are%20indeed%20middle-class.%20Still%2C%20many%20older%20Americans%20are%20worried%20about%20not%20being%20able%20to%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20all%20of%20those%20not-so-definitive%20measures%2C%20Walz%20and%20Vance%20both%20might%20have%20a%20legitimate%20claim%20to%20being%20middle-class%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20that%20doesn't%20really%20mean%20anything.%20But%20their%20broader%20messaging%20to%20that%20ill-defined%20cohort%20is%20part%20of%20a%20long%2C%20storied%20political%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAppealing%20to%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20American%20middle%20class%20has%20long%20been%20a%20go-to%20strategy%20for%20politicians%20looking%20for%20votes%20or%20ways%20to%20boost%20their%20popularity%2C%20so%20we%20shouldn't%20find%20it%20surprising%20that%20both%20vice-presidential%20candidates%20are%20doing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Lawrence%20R.%20Samuel%2C%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20American%20Middle%20Class%3A%20A%20Cultural%20History%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BBeyond%20drawing%20in%20citizens%20from%20both%20ends%20of%20the%20financial%20spectrum%20(even%20most%20rich%20and%20poor%20Americans%20consider%20themselves%20%26quot%3Bmiddle%20class%26quot%3B)%2C%20the%20term%20is%20linguistic%20currency%20for%20a%20host%20of%20positive%20values.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20consider%20yourself%20middle%20class%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-middle-class-jd-vance-tim-walz-are-targeting-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723972021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bf8ca3b4912df3ae1c61ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-middle-class-jd-vance-tim-walz-are-targeting-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Politicians%20love%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20middle%20class.%20But%20who%20that%20actually%20is%20remains%20murky.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CNoah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-middle-class-jd-vance-tim-walz-are-targeting-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Blog%3A%20Four%20Reasons%20Reading%20Drives%20Us%20Mad%20-%20And%2