ny%20debate%20so%20long%20as%20you%20preface%20your%20argument%20with%20the%20words%2C%20'Well%2C%20I%20know%20that's%20what%20you%20heard%20on%20a%20podcast%20but%20I%20read%20in%20a%20book...'.%20When%20your%20friends%20are%20raving%20about%20a%20new%20movie%2C%20you%20can%20declare%20with%20a%20sniff%2C%20'To%20be%20perfectly%20honest%2C%20the%20book%20is%20much%20better...'.%20Surrounding%20yourself%20with%20books%20can%20earn%20you%20the%20admiration%20of%20your%20peers.%20You%20don't%20even%20need%20to%20have%20read%20them%20-%20merely%20possessing%20a%20well-stocked%20bookcase%20can%20make%20you%20a%20sophisticate%20(ask%20any%20interior%20designer).%20In%20these%20times%20of%20snappy%20reels%2C%20clickbait%20headlines%2C%20and%20dwindling%20attention%20spans%2C%20book%20readers%20are%20revered%20as%20'Zen%20masters'%20who%20can%20ignore%20the%20lure%20of%20doomscrolling%20and%20immerse%20themselves%20in%20the%20textual%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20no%20wonder%20then%20that%20so%20many%20parents%20hope%20their%20children%20grow%20up%20to%20be%20readers%2C%20or%20that%20countless%20adults%20strive%20to%20adopt%20reading%20as%20a%20hobby.%20Yet%2C%20you%20rarely%20hear%20anyone%20talking%20about%20the%20undiagnosed%20emotional%20damage%20caused%20by%20books%20-%20anyone%20who%20has%20read%20%3Cem%3EA%20Little%20Life%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Hanya%20Yanagihara%20will%20know%20what%20I%20mean%20-%20and%20the%20pernicious%20effects%20of%20reading%20in%20general.%20It%20is%20about%20time%20someone%20acted%20to%20remedy%20this%20grave%20oversight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20Perpetual%20Despair...%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAllowing%20yourself%20to%20be%20consumed%20by%20a%20love%20for%20books%20can%20harm%20you%2C%20broadly%20speaking%2C%20in%20four%20significant%20ways.%20To%20begin%20with%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20you%20to%20be%20assailed%20by%20a%20sense%20of%20despair%2C%20a%20feeling%20of%20crushing%20hopelessness%20every%20time%20you%20enter%20a%20bookshop.%20As%20you%20browse%20the%20shelves%20and%20stack%20volumes%20in%20the%20crook%20of%20your%20arm%2C%20you%20realise%20you%20will%20never%20get%20around%20to%20reading%20all%20the%20books%20that%20call%20out%20to%20you.%20Some%20are%20able%20to%20make%20peace%20with%20this%20doleful%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20those%20of%20a%20more%20defiant%20disposition%2C%20refuse%20to%20be%20cowed.%20They%20redouble%20their%20efforts%2C%20but%20since%20reading%20capacity%20is%20constrained%20by%20physical%20limits%2C%20these%20efforts%20end%20up%20being%20channelled%20solely%20towards%20the%20acquisition%20of%20books.%20The%20Japanese%20have%20an%20elegant%20word%20to%20describe%20this%20condition%3A%20%3Cem%3Etsundoku%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20means%20a%20penchant%20for%20stockpiling%20books%20with%20the%20genuine%20intention%20to%20read%20them%20all%20-%20subject%20only%20to%20the%20minor%20requirement%20of%20first%20attaining%20immortality.%20If%20you%20are%20also%20afflicted%20with%20this%20malady%2C%20do%20not%20be%20disheartened.%20Karl%20Lagerfeld%20is%20said%20to%20have%20owned%20over%203%2C00%2C000%20books.%20At%20least%2C%20things%20are%20not%20as%20grim%20for%20you%20(I%20hope).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuilt%20Meets%20Snobbery%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20abundance%20of%20material%20naturally%20leads%20to%20the%20second%20pitfall%20of%20reading%3A%20experiencing%20guilt.%20No%20matter%20which%20book%20you%20pick%20up%2C%20you%20are%20sure%20to%20feel%20a%20twinge%20of%20regret%20for%20the%20ones%20you're%20compelled%20to%20set%20aside.%20Every%20time%20you%20pull%20out%20your%20favourite%20Agatha%20Christie%20or%20P.%20G.%20Wodehouse%20title%20from%20the%20bookshelf%2C%20you%20can%20hear%20your%20dusty%20copy%20of%20%3Cem%3EWar%20and%20Peace%3C%2Fem%3E%20tutting%20in%20disappointment.%20In%20the%20library%2C%20when%20you're%20lingering%20in%20the%20Young%20Adult%20fantasy%20section%20-%20'young'%20is%20relative%2C%20after%20all%20-%20you%20can%20feel%20%3Cem%3EGreat%20Expectations%3C%2Fem%3E%20glaring%20at%20you%20from%20across%20the%20aisle.%20Every%20breezy%20read%20-%20every%20literary%20guilty%20pleasure%20-%20is%20laced%20with%20the%20shame%20of%20having%20abandoned%20%3Cem%3EFar%20from%20the%20Madding%20Crowd%3C%2Fem%3E%20after%20a%20dozen%20pages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20large%20part%20of%20this%20contrition%20is%20attributable%20to%20the%20third%20ill%20effect%20of%20reading%3A%20snobbery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Struggle%20To%20'Belong'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20of%20bibliophiles%20can%20be%20alarmingly%20tribal%20and%20each%20clique%20has%20its%20idiosyncrasies.%20You%20have%20the%20acolytes%20of%20the%20Russian%20masters%20-%20a%20bleak%20lot%20who%20can%20be%20disqualified%20from%20their%20clan%20if%20they%20ever%20crack%20a%20smile.%20Crime%20fiction%20aficionados%20tend%20to%20sidle%20up%20to%20you%2C%20introduce%20themselves%2C%20and%20then%20lean%20in%20to%20whisper%2C%20%26quot%3BSo...%20what%20do%20you%20think%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20a%20body%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20devotees%20of%20speculative%20fiction%20can%20be%20identified%20by%20their%20pallid%20skin%2C%20thick%20glasses%2C%20and%20ability%20to%20talk%20for%20hours%20about%20the%20genealogy%20of%20dragons%3B%20and%20then%20there%20are%20the%20readers%20of%20business%20management%20books%2C%20who%20pride%20themselves%20on%20having%20no%20imagination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20group%20believes%20their%20reading%20habits%20to%20be%20loftier%20and%20they%20are%20all%20perpetually%20at%20odds%20with%20each%20other.%20Indeed%2C%20there%20is%20only%20one%20thing%20that%20unites%20them%3A%20a%20shared%20loathing%20for%20lovers%20of%20romance%20novels%2C%20and%2C%20let's%20be%20honest%2C%20you%20can%20see%20where%20they're%20coming%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20not%20throw%20in%20your%20lot%20with%20any%20one%20of%20these%20clubs%2C%20then%20you%20must%20forever%20contend%20with%20their%20tidal%20pulls%20as%20you%20chart%20your%20literary%20journey.%20As%20you%20flit%20from%20one%20genre%20to%20the%20next%2C%20you%20will%20be%20welcomed%20and%20then%20mocked%2C%20your%20choice%20of%20books%20forever%20questioned%20and%20dismissed%20as%20being%20inferior%20to%20a%20host%20of%20other%20suggestions.%20If%20you%20somehow%20muster%20the%20will%20to%20ignore%20these%20challenges%20and%20keep%20going%2C%20then%20you%20will%20eventually%20have%20to%20tackle%20the%20fourth%2C%20and%20most%20fatal%2C%20misfortune%20to%20befall%20a%20reader.%20You%20will%20begin%20to%20believe%20that%20you%2C%20too%2C%20can%20be%20a%20writer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Can%20I%20....%20Be%20A%20Writer%3F'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20spends%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20time%20reading%20books%20soon%20begins%20to%20harbour%20fantasies%20of%20writing%20one%20themselves.%20It%20is%20one%20of%20those%20immutable%20laws%20of%20nature%20(those%20who%20read%20poetry%20are%20-%20unfortunately%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20-%20especially%20susceptible%20to%20this%20affliction).%20This%20is%20one%20of%20life's%20greatest%20tragedies%20because%20writing%20is%20a%20masochistic%2C%20time-consuming%20and%20exhausting%20pursuit.%20When%20you%20choose%20to%20become%20a%20writer%2C%20the%20only%20people%20who%20suffer%20more%20than%20you%20are%20your%20friends%20and%20family%20members%20who%20have%20to%20read%20your%20early%20output.%20It%20is%20only%20because%20they%20pretend%20to%20enjoy%20it%20that%20you%20are%20encouraged%20to%20continue.%20Pick%20up%20any%20celebrated%20guide%20on%20the%20craft%20of%20writing%20-%20be%20it%20%3Cem%3EBird%20by%20Bird%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Anne%20Lamott%20or%20%3Cem%3EOn%20Writing%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20Stephen%20King%20-%20and%20it%20will%20tell%20you%20that%20as%20a%20writer%20you%20must%20persevere%3B%20you%20must%20write%20with%20dedication%20and%20doggedness%2C%20and%20perhaps%20one%20day%20you%20will%20be%20wildly%20successful%20and%20publish%20a%20manuscript%20that%20makes%20a%20tenth%20of%20the%20sales%20of%20the%20latest%20book%20by%20a%20social%20media%20celebrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20bookworms%20endure%20one%20or%20more%20of%20these%20ordeals%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20astonishingly%2C%20they%20continue%20to%20read.%20Books%20continue%20to%20exist%2C%20and%20some%20people%20still%20find%20the%20greatest%20joy%20in%20getting%20lost%20in%20their%20pages%2C%20in%20weaving%20stories%20of%20their%20own.Most%20bookworms%20endure%20one%20or%20more%20of%20these%20ordeals%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20astonishingly%2C%20they%20continue%20to%20read.%20As%20far%20as%20book%20lovers%20are%20concerned%2C%20that%20is%20a%20blessing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Rohan%20Banerjee%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20lawyer%20based%20in%20Mumbai)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723971960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fkd95c4go_reading_625x300_18_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fblog%2Ffour-reasons-reading-drives-us-mad-and-why-we-still-keep-at-it-6363465%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Most%20bookworms%20endure%20one%20or%20more%20of%20these%20ordeals%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20astonishingly%2C%20they%20continue%20to%20read.%20Most%20bookworms%20endure%20one%20or%20more%20of%20these%20ordeals%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20astonishingly%2C%20they%20continue%20to%20read.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fblog%2Ffour-reasons-reading-drives-us-mad-and-why-we-still-keep-at-it-6363465%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amit%20Shah%20launches%20Rs%201003cr%20development%20projects%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%20pushes%20for%20CAA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723971821000%2C%22vis