n%20border%2C%20has%20borne%20the%20brunt%20of%20constant%20fire%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Smoke%20billowed%20after%20a%20hit%20from%20a%20rocket%20fired%20from%20southern%20Lebanon%20over%20the%20Upper%20Galilee%20region%20in%20northern%20Israel%20on%20July%208%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ab9fb51a227600e6337465%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYaara%20Alfasi%20said%20cross-border%20fire%20from%20southern%20Lebanon%20to%20northern%20Israel%2C%20like%20the%20one%20pictured%20in%20the%20Upper%20Galilee%20region%2C%20affects%20his%20winery.%3Cp%3EJALAA%20MAREY%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20winery%20was%20declared%20a%20closed%20military%20area%20from%20October%20until%20November%2C%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20harvest%20season%2C%20and%20the%20winery's%20sales%20dropped%2070%E2%80%9380%25%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20now%2C%20he%20said%2C%20there%20is%20still%20%26quot%3Buncertainty%20as%20to%20whether%20we%20will%20be%20able%20to%20get%20to%20the%20vineyards%20because%20the%20security%20situation%20warms%20up%20and%20relaxes%20every%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20the%20market%20has%20gradually%20recovered%2C%20it%20is%20still%20far%20from%20what%20it%20was%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGal%20Yaniv%2C%20CEO%20of%20Pelter%20Winery%2C%20a%20family-owned%20business%20in%20the%20Golan%20Heights%2C%20finds%20himself%20in%20a%20similar%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20BI%20that%20most%20of%20the%20vineyards%20are%20on%20the%20Lebanese-Syrian%20border%2C%20and%20some%20are%20out%20of%20reach%20due%20to%20cross-border%20fires%20and%20explosions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDue%20to%20fires%20caused%20by%20Hezbollah%20missiles%2C