3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdad-died-massive-medical-debt-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAffiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20and%20terms%20apply%20to%20offers%20listed%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22writer%20michelle%20chikaonda%20poses%20in%20front%20of%20a%20vineyard%20on%20vacation%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6283d8ba65d1770019e4ad83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Michelle%20Chikaonda.%3Cp%3EMichelle%20Chikaonda%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMy%20dad%20died%20in%202018%2C%20and%20he%20spent%20his%20last%2013%20days%20in%20the%20ICU%20%E2%80%94%20which%20came%20with%20a%20massive%20bill.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMedical%20debt%20like%20this%20is%20one%20kind%20of%20unsecured%20debt%2C%20which%20goes%20away%20if%20it%20isn't%20covered%20by%20the%20estate.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDebt%20collectors%20are%20legally%20limited%20in%20how%20they%20are%20allowed%20to%20seek%20repayment%20after%20someone%20dies.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20father%20died%20of%20cancer%20in%20October%202018%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20small%20California%20town%20named%20Loma%20Linda%20%E2%80%94%20we%20were%20sent%20a%20massive%20ICU%20bill%20in%20his%20name%2C%20exactly%20one%20week%20after%20he'd%20died.%20He%20had%20been%20admitted%20to%20the%20ICU%20for%2013%20days%20after%20nearly%20two%20years%20with%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20was%20still%20figuring%20out%20the%20expensive%20logistics%20of%20getting%20his%20body%20repatriated%20to%20our%20home%20country%20of%20Malawi%2C%20and%20the%20bill%20felt%20unreal.%20It%20may%20as%20well%20have%20been%20Monopoly%20money%2C%20for%20how%20real%20the%20implied%20stacks%20of%20banknotes%20actually%20felt.%20My%20mother%20and%20I%20laughed%20bitterly%20as%20we%20sat%20together%20at%20the%20dinner%20table%2C%20in%20horrified%20awe%20at%20the%20absurdity%20of%20our%20essentially%20being%20billed%20for%20my%20father's%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nearly%2010%20pages%20of%20hospital%20itemizations%20detailing%20the%20technicalities%20of%20the%20final%2013%20days%20of%20my%20father's%20life%20forced%20me%20to%20realize%20the%20intimidating%20extent%20of%20knowledge%20I%20did%20not%20have%20about%20how%20to%20handle%20the%20financial%20affairs%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20regarding%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20of%20the%20recently%20deceased.%20I%20was%20even%20naive%20enough%20not%20to%20be%20aware%20that%20someone%20could%20still%20be%20medically%20billed%20after%20they%20died.%20That%20seemed%20nonsensical%2C%20but%20it%20is%20an%20absolute%20truth%20of%20the%20financial%20realities%20of%20death%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThus%20information%20and%20research%20became%20twin%20weapons%20in%20the%20months%20following%20my%20father's%20funeral.%20I%20knew%20that%20it%20would%20be%20easy%20for%20my%20family%20to%20be%20financially%20taken%20advantage%20of%20in%20that%20emotionally%20sensitive%20period%2C%20and%20I%20was%20determined%20to%20ensure%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20As%20I%20was%20the%20only%20member%20of%20my%20family%20who%20was%20still%20a%20US%20resident%2C%20I%20spent%20several%20painstaking%20months%20making%20phone%20calls%20and%20mailing%20out%20copies%20of%20my%20father's%20death%20certificate%20by%20myself%2C%20as%20I%20closed%20out%20his%20American%20financial%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20nearly%20five%20years%20since%20Dad's%20death%2C%20I%20have%20seen%20stories%20both%20frustrating%20and%20heartbreaking%20about%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20bereaved%20families%20have%20not%20only%20been%20financially%20lost%20after%20a%20loved%20one's%20passing%2C%20but%20have%20been%20taken%20advantage%20of%20by%20unscrupulous%20companies%20looking%20to%20maximize%20their%20earnings%20by%20razor-thin%20margins%20of%20ethics%20and%20legality.%20Here%20are%20what%20I%20consider%20to%20be%20the%20five%20most%20important%20things%20for%20people%20to%20know%20about%20what%20they%20most%20likely%20do%2C%20or%20do%20not%2C%20owe%20debtors%20upon%20a%20loved%20one's%20passing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Debt%20doesn't%20go%20away%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20someone%20has%20to%20pay%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fask-cfpb%2Fdoes-a-persons-debt-go-away-when-they-die-en-1463%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConsumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20person's%20debts%20are%20assumed%20by%20their%20estate%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20simply%20any%20money%20and%20property%20left%20behind%20after%20their%20death%20%E2%80%94%20and%20any%20outstanding%20debts%20should%20be%20paid%20off%20by%20what%20remains%20in%20the%20person's%20estate.%20This%20is%20handled%20either%20by%20the%20executor%20of%20the%20estate%2C%20named%20in%20the%20deceased%20person's%20will%2C%20or%20by%20a%20government-appointed%20administrator%20if%20the%20person%20died%20without%20a%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20very%20limited%20cases%20where%20someone%20else%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20spouse%20or%20parent%20%E2%80%94%20may%20be%20required%20to%20pay%20off%20certain%20debts%20of%20the%20deceased.%20In%20community%20property%20states%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20where%20spouses%20share%20joint%20ownership%20of%20certain%20debts%20undertaken%20during%20their%20marriage%20%E2%80%94%20a%20surviving%20spouse%20may%20be%20required%20to%20pay%20off%20certain%20debts.%20Confirm%20state-specific%20requirements%20to%20ensure%20only%20what%20is%20legally%20owed%20is%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Unsecured%20debts%20generally%20remain%20the%20property%20of%20the%20deceased%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-loans%2Fbest-unsecured-loans%5C%22%3EUnsecured%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20debt%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fbest-private-student-loans%5C%22%3Estudent%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-loans%2Fbest-personal-loans%5C%22%3Epersonal%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20medical%20bills.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.experian.com%2Fblogs%2Fask-experian%2Fwhat-happens-to-debt-when-you-die%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExperian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20these%20should%20be%20handled%20by%20the%20estate%20if%20there%20is%20any%20money%20remaining%20to%20pay%20those%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20whether%20those%20debts%20are%20paid%20off%20is%20determined%20by%20the%20legal%20order%20in%20which%20estate%20disbursements%20are%20required%20to%20be%20handled.%20If%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20person%20dies%20in%20a%20state%20where%20survivors%20are%20paid%20out%20first%2C%20there%20may%20be%20no%20money%20remaining%20in%20the%20estate%20to%20pay%20off%20unsecured%20debts.%20Ensure%20the%20executor%20or%20administrator%20of%20the%20estate%20confirms%20specific%20state%20requirements%20before%20paying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Secured%20debts%20must%20be%20paid%20off%20by%20someone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20secured%20loans%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3Emortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20auto%20loans.%20If%20they%20aren't%20paid%20by%20the%20estate%20or%20by%20someone%20else%2C%20the%20asset%20backing%20them%20%E2%80%94%20the%20house%20or%20the%20car%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20claimed%20by%20the%20lending%20institution.%20Houses%20and%20cars%20often%20have%20co-signers%20for%20loans%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20to%20understand%20who%20will%20be%20responsible%20for%20that%20debt%20and%20what%20happens%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20plan%20to%20maintain%20use%20of%20them%20after%20their%20loved%20one's%20death.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Federal%20student%20loans%20are%20discharged%20%E2%80%94%20private%20student%20loans%20usually%20aren't%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20die%20with%20federal%20student%20loan%20debt%2C%20those%20loans%20will%20be%20discharged.%20Private%20lenders%2C%20however%2C%20may%20still%20require%20the%20loan%20be%20repaid%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20the%20case%20of%20certain%20parent-student%20loans%2C%20or%20other%20types%20of%20co-signed%20student%20debt.%20The%20estate%20administrator%20should%20contact%20the%20lending%20institution%20directly%20to%20find%20out%20what%20is%20applicable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20The%20law%20restricts%20debt%20collection%20after%20death%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emotional%20vulnerability%20of%20survivors%20of%20the%20deceased%20can%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20make%20them%20ideal%20targets%20for%20aggressive%20debt%20collectors%20intent%20on%20seeing%20the%20debts%20of%20the%20deceased%20repaid%20by%20any%20means%20necessary.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconsumer.ftc.gov%2Farticles%2Fdebts-and-deceased-relatives%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Trade%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20gives%20detailed%20information%20on%20what%20debt%20collectors%20may%20and%20may%20not%20do%20in%20order%20to%20collect%20on%20a%20loved%20one's%20death%2C%20especially%20to%20protect%20against%20manipulative%20and%20potentially%20deceptive%20practices%20targeted%20at%20loved%20ones%20willing%20to%20do%20whatever%20they're%20made%20to%20believe%20is%20required%20to%20settle%20a%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandling%20a%20loved%20one's%20debts%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20their%20passing%20can%20feel%20daunting%20and%20even%20retraumatizing.%20I%20discovered%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20my%20father's%20death%20just%20how%20bureaucratically%20difficult%20it%20is%20to%20make%20the%20biological%20fact%20of%20a%20loved%20one's%20death%20a%20legal%20one%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20regarding%20their%20debts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20father's%20ICU%20bill%20was%20eventually%20written%20off%20after%20several%20letters%20and%20phone%20calls%20between%20myself%20and%20the%20hospital%20billing%20office%3B%20the%20last%20letters%20I%20wrote%20to%20the%20hospital%20were%20to%20all%20of%20his%20various%20medical%20teams%2C%20thanking%20them%20for%20their%20care%20in%20the%20worst%2013%20days%20of%20me%20and%20my%20family's%20lives.%20With%20that%2C%20the%20emotional%20process%20of%20moving%20forward%20could%20finally%20begin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20May%202023.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdad-died-massive-medical-debt-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723933381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64